C++ for webapplications

Like JSP or. NET "idea", combines the capabilities of a real programming language CHTML with the ease of modern web development.

Each "page" consists of an HTML equivalent, and a "controller", which implements the logic. Of course it is also possible C + + code directly embedded into the HTML page and connect with the business logic.
The management of user sessions will be activated on demand and is associated with the use of a database back-ends. The database access is encapsulated and is part of the overall concept.

Like "on Rails & Co." There are tools that support in managing the websites and their controllers.
Is a website developed, it will be compiled into real machine code and thus made free from any interference, directly on the CPU. - Quick it's not easy!
